The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Bengal fall to Meghalaya 

 - Bus carrying athletes turns turtle, 20 hurt 

OUR CORRESPONDENT

Guwahati: Meghalaya on Sunday stunned runners-up Bengal with an incredible 4-1 victory. Three goals in the final six minutes, including one before the final whistle, helped Meghalaya register a 4-1 win over their opponents. With the scores levelled at 1-1 till the 62nd minute, Bengal went all out but it was Meghalaya who did all the scoring. 

Niwan Galphoh, who had also scored the first goal in the 38th minute, found the net for the second time in the 84th minute. Gauranga Dutta scored the only goal for Bengal in the 62nd minute. 

What followed was even more riveting. Four minutes later, K. Lyngching made it 3-1 and Romeo Sukhleim made it 4-1 in the 89th minute, leaving Bengal shell-shocked and Meghalaya delirious. 

Hosts Assam, too, won laurels on the field. The Assam men and womens team defeated Tamil Nadu 2-0 and Orissa 1-0, respectively. Assams D. Singh scored the first goal in 27th minute and Ajit Singh made it 2-0 in injury time. 

Defending champions Manipur survived a scare in the womens event against Orissa, forcing a 1-1 draw with only two minutes to go for the final whistle. 

At least 20 people, including 16 members of the Services squad and two sportspersons from Andhra Pradesh, were injured in a bus accident near Sarusajai Stadium Complex here Sunday. The bus carrying the athelets hit a road divider and turned turtle. 




